version_description:
• The latest release of Cloud Console enables customers to view App Engine and Compute Engine logs to make troubleshooting application and resource issues easier on the go. Simply tap the menu button on a dashboard card, App Engine version, or Compute Engine VM to access the log viewer for that resource.
• Cloud Console is now a universal app, adding native iPad support.
• Fixed an issue where it was not possible to dismiss the SSH view or access special keys.
• Additional bug fixes and stability improvements.
Bug fixes and stability improvements for iOS 7 users.

• Google Compute Engine: You can now view your disks, snapshots, and zones; create, delete, attach, and detach disks; and create and delete snapshots.
• Billing: You can now see your billing overview, your promotions and credits, and export your billing information to a Google Cloud Storage bucket.
• Supports split screen on iPads running iOS 9.0 or higher.
• Cloud Console iOS now requires iOS 8.0 or higher.

• Set a passcode to lock access to your resources in the Cloud Console iOS app. From the navigation drawer, tap "Settings" then "Passcode settings" to configure it.
• View and edit the user, group, and service account permissions on your projects.
• Access logs even more easily by selecting "Logs" in the navigation drawer.
• Fixed an issue where the help pages would not load.
• Fixed an issue where overflow menus did not work on iPad.
Fix a possible crash when removing an account from the passcode screen.

The latest version of Google Cloud Console for iOS adds several additional Stackdriver capabilities, including Error Reporting (with notifications) and Trace. Receive optional push notifications on your mobile device when Stackdriver detects a new error in your application, and view latency trace reports for any of your application's end points, as well as A/B latency comparisons.
Bug fixes in Logs feature, including better support for custom logs.

Minor update to display of App Engine Versions.
Various bug fixes.
Various stability and bug fixes. Minimum OS requirement increased to iOS 9.0.

• Improved UI for incident monitoring.
• Localized into 9 new languages.
• Bug fixes.

•Traffic splitting is now supported. You may use traffic splitting to distribute a percentage of traffic to two or more versions of your App Engine applications.
•Various bug fixes.

• Access Cloud Shell to perform any Google Cloud (gcloud) operation.
• New welcome experience on first launch to introduce new users to the app.
• Continued bug fixes and performance improvements.
Redesigned the help and support experience. Get the right support for your Google Cloud Platform projects from the app.

* Improved navigation with quicker access to Cloud Shell and easy account switching.
* Continued bug fixes and other improvements.

* Added support of dark mode.
* Continued bug fixes and other improvements.

• You can now copy/paste and adjust preferences for text size, font, and color theme in Cloud Shell.
• This release also includes bug fixes and other improvements.
